Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
analyze_paths_by_hier_port(25.10)            analyze_paths_by_hier_port(25.10)

Name
       analyze_paths_by_hier_port  -  Helps  you  to automatically group paths
       based on each hierarchical port of the given instances

Syntax
       analyze_paths_by_hier_port

       [-help]

       {{-gen_hier_file  <string>  [-out_file  <string>]}  |  {-load_hier_file
       <string>}}

       [-master <string>]

       Helps  you to automatically group paths based on each hierarchical port
       of the given instances. You can use this command to perform the  timing
       results  analysis  of a hierarchical design. For example, while looking
       at the setup/hold time at the same time of each port.

       The command can be applied wherever the user loads  timing  report.  To
       delete   the   path   categories   created   by   this   command,   use
       delete_path_category. For more information on creating path categories,
       see "Creating Path Categories" in the Debugging Timing Results  chapter
       of Innovus User Guide.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each analyze_paths_by_hier_port parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man analyze_paths_by_hier_port

       -gen_hier_file <string>
              Generates  hier  ports  fanin/fanout  file  when the database is
              available based on the given InstanceName_list. Then  uses  that
              file to create the categories.

       -load_hier_file <string>
              Uses  a  previously  saved hier ports fanin/fanout file when the
              database is not available.

       -master <string>
              Specifies that the timing paths should be categorized  only  for
              the specified master category.

       -out_file <string>
              Specifies the generated hier ports fanin/fanout file name.

Example
       The  following  command categorizes paths based on hierarchical port of
       the instance DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST:

       analyze_paths_by_hier_port -gen_hier_file DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST

Related Information
       The Debugging Timing Results chapter of the Innovus  User  Guide  docu-
       ment.

